Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["14. Summary", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"5d010cfd-8c1b-490f-a6ad-edfe5fff3097"],

Cell["\<\
This notebook derives the cubic T-matrix from the FULL elastodynamic Green\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s tensor (Kupradze representation), including both static \
near-field and radiation terms.

Key results:
\[Bullet] Smooth polynomial: G^s_ij = \[CapitalPhi](r^2) \[Delta]_ij + \
\[CapitalPsi](r^2) x_i x_j
\[Bullet] \[CapitalPhi] and \[CapitalPsi] contain ALL frequency-dependent terms
\[Bullet] I_ijkl = A \[Delta]_ij\[Delta]_kl + B(perm) + C E_ijkl has cubic \
anisotropy (C \[NotEqual] 0)
\[Bullet] Four amplification factors (vs three for sphere)
\[Bullet] Cubic splitting \[CapitalDelta]\[Mu]*_diag \[Minus] \[CapitalDelta]\
\[Mu]*_off \[Proportional] T_3
\[Bullet] A, B, C are complex at finite \[Omega]: imaginary parts = radiation \
damping
\[Bullet] Born limit (a \[Rule] 0): all contrasts reduce to bare values\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"962ebba7-333b-4040-8701-ff907fbe9ee5"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
},
WindowSize->{1728, 1056},
WindowMargins->{{0, Automatic}, {Automatic, 0}},
WindowTitle->"Cubic T-Matrix: Full Green's Tensor",
FrontEndVersion->"14.3 for Mac OS X ARM (64-bit) (July 8, 2025)",
StyleDefinitions->"Default.nb",
ExpressionUUID->"b507329c-a439-4a5e-aa69-42cc4b8b2fc0"
]
